                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1410-1">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note type="description" xml:id="abstract-en-1410">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1410">Pethion</persName> was a Zoroastrian
                        convert who, with his uncle the monk <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1520">Yazdin</persName>, preached in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/121">the region
                            of the lower Zab</placeName>. His hagiography was connected to that of an aristocratic
                        father and daughter pair whom he helped to convert:<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1119">Adorhormizd</persName> and his daughter <persName ref=" http://syriaca.org/person/1129">Anahid</persName>. Pethion was martyred
                        under <persName>Yazdegerd II</persName>.</note>
                    <note type="abstract">A Zoroastrian convert to Christianity martyred during the reign of <persName>Yazdegerd II</persName>.</note>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1410-1">AMS, II, 604- 31 ; BHO, 923- 26; J . Corluy, dans AB 7 (1888), 8- 44.
Suhadii', II, 373- 80.
Hoffmann, Ausziige, 61- 68.
Fiey, Mossoul chretienne, 123- 25.
Poeme sur lui : Ms. Mingana syr. 214, fol. 131a- 132a.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1410-1" source="#bib1410-10">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Pethion is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/292">Pethion, Adorhormizd, Anahid, and Yazdin (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
